  Therefore it makes use of several implemented inverse kinematics approaches at the first order differential level.

  redundancy resolution and priority-based methods.

description: Bindings between openrave's controller interface and ROS's action lib interface for controlling robots.

name: openrave_calibration
description: Package uses openrave planning and the robot_calibration stacks to calibrate a robot's sensors. The calibration only depends on the openrave/collada descriptions, therefore it is meant to be a relatively simple way of calibrating new robots with one-click.

name: openrave_database
description: Uses ROS to parallelize the database generation processes inside OpenRAVE.

name: openrave_msgs
description: Contains ROS messages and services that are commonly used in the openrave_planning stack.

name: openrave_planning
description:
This stack offers OpenRAVE-related bindings.
    Maintained by the JSK lab at University of Tokyo.

name: openrave_robot_control
description:
Contains messages, services, and OpenRAVE clients to interface to robot hardware.

    - librobot_control - openrave plugin for ros client to talk to robot services
    - openravecontroller.h - base class for robot server using services
    - tfsender - given joint positions of the robot, sends the correct tf frames

    For more information on how to use this inside the openrave framework, see:
    http://openrave.programmingvision.com/wiki/index.php/ROS:ControllingRobots

name: openrave_robot_filter
description: Utilities for filtering the robot out of sensor data

name: openrave_sensors
description: Contains openrave plugins that connect send and recieve ROS messages allowing OpenRAVE to communicate with the ROS world better.
